-- India May Purchase 10 Boeing Planes for $3.5 Billion, ET Reports
-- B y   S u p r o t i p   G h o s h
-- 2010-09-22T01:40:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-22/india-may-purchase-10-boeing-transport-planes-for-3-5-billion-et-reports.html
India may sign a $3.5 billion order
for 10 Boeing Co. C-17 Globemaster military transport aircraft
for use by the nation’s airforce, the Economic Times reported,
without saying where it got the information. The order is likely
to be signed during U.S. President Barack Obama’s planned visit
to India in November.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Suprotip Ghosh in Mumbai at 
